summary: This is an email chain between FBI agents discussing the Office of the Chief Medical Examiner (OCME) delaying the finalization of Jeffrey Epstein's autopsy report. The delay is to prevent the release of sensitive information, including video, guard names, and interviews, to Epstein's family and lawyers until the SDNY can review and redact the material.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: The email discusses the autopsy report for Jeffrey Epstein, which is being delayed by the OCME to prevent sensitive information from being released to his family and lawyers.

events.title: Email regarding Epstein autopsy report delay
events.description: An email chain discusses the Office of the Chief Medical Examiner (OCME) deciding not to finalize Jeffrey Epstein's autopsy reports at that time to prevent sensitive information from being released.

keyFacts: The Office of the Chief Medical Examiner (OCME) delayed finalizing Jeffrey Epstein's autopsy report to prevent sensitive information from being released to his family and lawyers.
Sensitive material mentioned includes video, guard names, and interviews related to Epstein's death.
The SDNY assigned an Assistant U.S. Attorney (AUSA) to work with the OCME to determine what information should be removed or redacted before the report is finalized.
The email chain involves communication between FBI agents, indicating federal law enforcement's involvement in managing the information related to Epstein's death.
